<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef">
  <CalDefFileVersion>4</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <Date>03/26/2020</Date>
    <Description>Initial Release of the calibration based on CRs 2287852, 2331035, and 2425907.</Description>
    <Author>Tatiana R. Risovas</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>04/09/2020</Date>
    <Description>Initial Release of the calibration based on CRs 2287852, 2331035, and 2425907. Review Cal Descriptions as per Ginnard and Greg recommendations.</Description>
    <Author>Tatiana R. Risovas</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>05/18/2020</Date>
    <Description>Add Trip Page Cal, Story 213188</Description>
    <Author>Tatiana R. Risovas</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>09/22/2020</Date>
    <Description>Change the cal change for: Side Slip angle (degrees) cals and Max torque. Specifically made the following updates: Changed the cal datatype from FLOAT to an Integer for the following cals as well updated minimum and maximum ranges as required for these cals: OFF_ROAD_APP_TILT_PEAK_PITCH_ANGLE, OFF_ROAD_APP_TILT_PEAK_ROLL_ANGLE, and OFF_ROAD_APP_SIDE_SLIP_ANGLE_MIN_RETENTION_VALUE. Also, updated the range for the min and maximum range for the following cals: OFF_ROAD_APP_G_FORCE_FRICTION_CIRCLE_RANGE, OFF_ROAD_APP_MAX_TORQUE, OFF_ROAD_APP_SIDE_SLIP_ANGLE_ABSOLUTE_SLIP_LAT_ACCEL_TEST, OFF_ROAD_APP_SIDE_SLIP_ANGLE_ABSOLUTE_SLIP_SPEED_TEST, OFF_ROAD_APP_SIDE_SLIP_ANGLE_MAX_DRIFT_ANGLE_VALUE, OFF_ROAD_APP_SIDE_SLIP_ANGLE_MAX_GAUGE_VALUE to be to more realistic ranges required. </Description>
    <Author>Tatiana R. Risovas</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>10/14/2020</Date>
    <Description>Delete OFF_ROAD_APP_STANDARD_ECUS_PRESENT calibration, add the OFF_ROAD_APP_TCCM_PRESENT cal.</Description>
    <Author>Tatiana R. Risovas</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="The purpose of the calibration is to enable the TILT Peak Pitch Angle Information for Off Road App Content." Name="OFF_ROAD_APP_TILT_PEAK_PITCH_ANGLE" References="Off Road App STS, Off Road App FNC" Usage="MID,HIGH,VCU,ENTRY_VCU,GLOBALB">
    <CalID>_AI1IYWI3EeqZFuyo2712Fg</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Integer>
      <Value>20</Value>
      <MinValue>-45</MinValue>
      <MaxValue>45</MaxValue>
      <Units>degrees</Units>
      <Resolution>1.0</Resolution>
    </Integer>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="The purpose of the calibration is to enable the TILT Peak Roll Angle Information for Off Road App Content." Name="OFF_ROAD_APP_TILT_PEAK_ROLL_ANGLE" References="Off Road App STS, Off Road App FNC" Usage="MID,HIGH,VCU,ENTRY_VCU,GLOBALB">
    <CalID>_IQ9NAWI4EeqZFuyo2712Fg</CalID>
